<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="behave-v">behave <strong><em>v</em></strong> ★</h1>
<p>英 /bɪ'heɪv/    美 /bɪ'heɪv/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>表现</strong></h4>
<p>to act in a particular way(act)：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He was a little boy, but he <strong>behaved as if / though</strong> he was an adult.
他是一个小男孩，但却表现得像个大人。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>(使) 举止规矩；(使) 表现得体</strong></h4>
<p>to act in a correct or appropriate way：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>badly- / well-behaved</strong> children 
不守规矩/守规矩的孩子</p></div>

<ul>
<li>behave oneself:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Students should be encouraged to develop good habits and better behave themselves. 
应当鼓励学生养成良好的习惯，行为更加规矩。</p><footer>2011 浙江</footer></div>

<h2 id="_2">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>Tom, <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ (规矩点). Did you forget the school rules?  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. behave yourself  </p></div>